18
00:00:12,415 --> 00:00:15,415
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,525
<i>A people enslaved!</i>

20
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:24,028
<i>To locate the abducted colonists
of a peace-loving world,</i>

21
00:00:24,111 --> 00:00:27,490
<i>the Jedi infiltrated the slaver planet
of Zygerria,</i>

22
00:00:27,740 --> 00:00:30,368
<i>only to be captured by its ambitious queen,</i>

23
00:00:30,451 --> 00:00:33,454
<i>who plots to rebuild her empire
of oppression.</i>

24
00:00:33,746 --> 00:00:39,377
<i>Now even Obi-Wan Kenobi
must come to terms with a life in chains.</i>

25
00:00:51,138 --> 00:00:55,142
Obi-Wan Kenobi, once a Jedi master,

26
00:00:55,184 --> 00:00:57,478
now a Jedi slave.

27
00:00:59,814 --> 00:01:01,148
Pitiful.

28
00:01:29,093 --> 00:01:31,387
Keep eyes on your toil, skug!

29
00:01:35,516 --> 00:01:39,145
Everything about this place
is designed to shatter the will.

30
00:01:39,186 --> 00:01:42,189
It has already begun to affect
these poor people.

31
00:01:43,691 --> 00:01:45,651
Speech is forbidden!

32
00:01:45,818 --> 00:01:48,362
I'm sorry. It won't happen again.

33
00:01:48,404 --> 00:01:50,031
There will be punishment!

34
00:01:50,656 --> 00:01:53,492
No, stop, it's my mistake!
Leave him alone!

35
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:02,418
Now a slave gives me commands?

36
00:02:03,336 --> 00:02:04,337
Beg!

37
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:07,923
Beg me before this one dies
because of you!

38
00:02:10,176 --> 00:02:13,054
Please. Forgive me, Master.

39
00:02:20,353 --> 00:02:23,731
Keep away from me.
Jedi only make things worse.

40
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:45,252
<i>Long have Sith empires been built
upon the backs of slaves.</i>

41
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:50,591
<i>To carry on this tradition,
we will require millions.</i>

42
00:02:51,258 --> 00:02:56,263
I assure you, the Queen's defiance
will not sour your plans, Master.

43
00:02:56,764 --> 00:03:00,267
<i>If she fails to see the error of her ways,</i>

44
00:03:00,351 --> 00:03:02,269
<i>end her rule.</i>

45
00:03:21,455 --> 00:03:24,208
Have you considered my offer, Skywalker?

46
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,752
If you vow loyalty to me,

47
00:03:26,794 --> 00:03:29,463
I will free your friends.

48
00:03:29,755 --> 00:03:31,799
It's not an easy decision.

49
00:03:31,882 --> 00:03:34,468
Hmm, curious.

50
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:36,679
I thought the Jedi were selfless,

51
00:03:36,762 --> 00:03:39,724
placing the needs of others
before their own.

52
00:03:48,566 --> 00:03:51,235
My Queen, I bring word.

53
00:03:51,318 --> 00:03:53,612
Count Dooku is on his way here.

54
00:03:53,654 --> 00:03:56,782
Ah, sooner than anticipated.

55
00:03:56,824 --> 00:03:59,452
Make preparations for his arrival.

56
00:04:01,454 --> 00:04:03,497
So even you have a master.

57
00:04:03,998 --> 00:04:06,292
Dooku is not my master!

58
00:04:07,293 --> 00:04:10,629
Perhaps you should not attend
this meeting.

59
00:04:10,671 --> 00:04:12,423
Can I trust you not to run away?

60
00:04:15,050 --> 00:04:17,261
I don't run away from anything,
Your Highness.

61
00:04:23,017 --> 00:04:24,143
Hmm...

62
00:04:37,573 --> 00:04:40,367
Get off, you miserable tin can!

63
00:04:44,622 --> 00:04:46,874
Get down there and find that Jedi.

64
00:04:46,957 --> 00:04:48,375
Yes, sir.

65
00:05:02,681 --> 00:05:05,434
Nice work, pal. You find Ahsoka?

66
00:05:14,985 --> 00:05:17,238
I wasn't expecting you, Count.

67
00:05:17,738 --> 00:05:19,698
Not without an invitation.

68
00:05:19,782 --> 00:05:23,619
But I was invited, by your faithful advisor.

69
00:05:25,746 --> 00:05:30,084
He's concerned over
how attached you've become to Skywalker.

70
00:05:30,459 --> 00:05:33,170
Skywalker is a symbol of my...

71
00:05:33,254 --> 00:05:36,090
Our power to enslave even Jedi.

72
00:05:36,423 --> 00:05:38,759
Your power over him is an illusion.

73
00:05:38,843 --> 00:05:42,304
You forget, I was once a Jedi myself.

74
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:45,558
You have little in common with Anakin.

75
00:05:47,434 --> 00:05:51,063
Please, hear my plans for the Jedi,
then decide.

76
00:05:51,939 --> 00:05:56,110
Right now,
at my facility in the Kadavo system,

77
00:05:56,151 --> 00:05:58,946
Obi-Wan Kenobi is in despair.

78
00:05:59,780 --> 00:06:01,115
I'm listening.

79
00:06:01,198 --> 00:06:03,492
Kenobi is coming to realize,

80
00:06:03,576 --> 00:06:06,453
perhaps for the first time in his life,

81
00:06:06,537 --> 00:06:09,999
that his efforts to help others
will only injure them.

82
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:19,008
As plans for escape
and hopes of rescue fade,

83
00:06:19,091 --> 00:06:22,136
the gnawing fear
that he will never be able to take action

84
00:06:22,469 --> 00:06:24,847
will grow in Kenobi's heart.

85
00:06:27,016 --> 00:06:30,269
To ease the burden of his fellow slaves,

86
00:06:30,311 --> 00:06:33,439
defiance will become compliance.

87
00:06:34,398 --> 00:06:37,860
When Kenobi realizes
he cannot help those around him,

88
00:06:37,943 --> 00:06:42,990
his spirit will break and he will be mine.

89
00:06:44,241 --> 00:06:48,203
If such Jedi as Skywalker and Kenobi
can fall,

90
00:06:48,287 --> 00:06:50,539
how many others will follow?

91
00:06:50,623 --> 00:06:53,000
Hmm?

92
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:57,588
Imagine...
Imagine an army of Jedi in your service.

93
00:06:58,172 --> 00:07:01,008
Zygerria will be invincible!

94
00:07:01,508 --> 00:07:05,137
A most ambitious plan, Your Highness.

95
00:07:05,179 --> 00:07:09,475
Only my goal is not the enslavement
of the Jedi Order,

96
00:07:09,516 --> 00:07:11,810
but its extermination.

97
00:07:11,852 --> 00:07:16,065
I have come to supervise their execution,
perform it if necessary.

98
00:07:16,774 --> 00:07:18,067
Now,

99
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:20,027
summon Skywalker.

100
00:07:34,959 --> 00:07:37,086
Well, hello, Master.

101
00:07:37,169 --> 00:07:38,545
Took you long enough.

102
00:07:39,213 --> 00:07:41,632
Well, I knew you had a nice view.

103
00:07:57,564 --> 00:07:58,565
Are you okay?

104
00:07:59,066 --> 00:08:01,610
I sense a disturbance in the Force.

105
00:08:01,735 --> 00:08:04,113
It's Dooku. I need you to get our ship.

106
00:08:04,196 --> 00:08:05,906
Here, take this com link.

107
00:08:06,115 --> 00:08:07,574
Where are you going?

108
00:08:07,658 --> 00:08:09,576
The Queen knows where Obi-Wan is.

109
00:08:09,618 --> 00:08:12,079
Hold on to that com link
and wait for my signal.

110
00:08:14,581 --> 00:08:16,125
Come on, Artoo.

111
00:08:19,586 --> 00:08:22,923
I have no desire to end Skywalker's life.

112
00:08:23,007 --> 00:08:27,011
He has become a valuable asset to me
and my throne.

113
00:08:27,469 --> 00:08:30,139
Your compliance is not optional.

114
00:08:30,222 --> 00:08:32,683
I command you to kill Skywalker.

115
00:08:32,766 --> 00:08:36,437
I will not be ordered about
in my own palace, Count!

116
00:08:36,979 --> 00:08:41,942
If you won't do my bidding,
perhaps your prime minister will.

117
00:08:41,984 --> 00:08:44,486
Atai, what does he mean?

118
00:08:44,611 --> 00:08:48,157
I'm sorry, Your Majesty,
but the Count is right.

119
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:50,451
The Jedi should die.

120
00:08:50,576 --> 00:08:52,828
You're not fit to be queen any longer.

121
00:08:53,495 --> 00:08:55,789
Atai, you traitor!

122
00:08:55,873 --> 00:08:58,834
I'll make you both pay for this treachery.

123
00:09:05,507 --> 00:09:09,386
Punishment for a slave
who disobeys her master.

124
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,930
That's enough, Dooku!

125
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:17,061
Skywalker.

126
00:09:19,730 --> 00:09:23,192
I see the Queen has given you a long leash.

127
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:27,112
One more step and I will end her life.

128
00:09:27,154 --> 00:09:30,115
Why would you think I care
about this slaver scum?

129
00:09:30,824 --> 00:09:31,992
Indeed.

130
00:09:59,686 --> 00:10:01,230
The Queen!

131
00:10:01,313 --> 00:10:03,107
She was murdered by the Jedi.

132
00:10:07,694 --> 00:10:09,488
That's our signal. Let's get going.

133
00:10:21,542 --> 00:10:22,960
Take your vengeance!

134
00:10:44,064 --> 00:10:45,357
Your Highness.

135
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,151
No escape

136
00:10:48,318 --> 00:10:50,404
for any of us.

137
00:10:50,696 --> 00:10:52,322
Where is Obi-Wan?

138
00:10:52,447 --> 00:10:53,866
Tell me.

139
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,952
Kadavo system.

140
00:10:57,035 --> 00:10:59,663
You were right, Skywalker.

141
00:11:01,915 --> 00:11:04,084
I am a slave.

142
00:11:04,251 --> 00:11:06,753
Just as you are.

143
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:41,622
Someone wishes to speak with you.

144
00:11:43,498 --> 00:11:45,209
<i>Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>

145
00:11:45,292 --> 00:11:48,086
<i>In chains once again, I see.</i>

146
00:11:48,128 --> 00:11:49,296
Count Dooku.

147
00:11:49,671 --> 00:11:52,090
Still afraid to get your hands dirty?

148
00:11:52,132 --> 00:11:55,719
<i>I would gladly make an exception
in your case, my friend.</i>

149
00:11:56,094 --> 00:12:01,391
I wanted to say a proper farewell
before Keeper Agruss puts you to death.

150
00:12:22,329 --> 00:12:25,249
Keeper, the slave ship <i>Tecora</i>
is making an unscheduled landing

151
00:12:25,332 --> 00:12:26,875
on platform two-four.

152
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:28,669
<i>Skywalker.</i>

153
00:12:44,059 --> 00:12:45,644
So much for our ride home.

154
00:12:45,686 --> 00:12:46,687
What now?

155
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:49,356
We get through the old fashioned way.

156
00:12:52,651 --> 00:12:56,029
<i>Kenobi, tell your young friend, Skywalker,</i>

157
00:12:56,154 --> 00:12:57,823
<i>if he does not surrender,</i>

158
00:12:58,115 --> 00:13:01,368
<i>the slaves will be terminated in his name.</i>

159
00:13:05,038 --> 00:13:07,040
<i>Anakin! I'm glad to see you,</i>

160
00:13:07,124 --> 00:13:09,584
<i>but I'm afraid our host feels otherwise.</i>

161
00:13:09,876 --> 00:13:11,586
You can't make everyone happy, Master.

162
00:13:12,713 --> 00:13:15,549
<i>They're threatening to kill the slaves
unless you surrender.</i>

163
00:13:15,590 --> 00:13:18,093
It's good to see
you're always ready to negotiate.

164
00:13:18,176 --> 00:13:20,429
But I've had enough bargaining
with slave drivers.

165
00:13:20,512 --> 00:13:23,807
<i>Anakin, you must realize
this is a fight you cannot win alone.</i>

166
00:13:24,391 --> 00:13:26,143
Who said I was alone?

167
00:13:37,821 --> 00:13:41,366
Keeper, a fleet of warships has dropped out
of hyperspace in sector six.

168
00:13:41,408 --> 00:13:43,201
Jedi reinforcements!

169
00:13:48,415 --> 00:13:51,418
Wolf leader to wolf pack,
accelerate to attack speed.

170
00:13:51,710 --> 00:13:53,211
This is Warthog, we're going in.

171
00:14:00,344 --> 00:14:01,803
Rex! Now!

172
00:14:01,887 --> 00:14:03,263
About time.

173
00:14:12,147 --> 00:14:14,149
Those towers are ray shielded.

174
00:14:15,776 --> 00:14:18,278
I hope you told Master Plo
not to destroy this facility

175
00:14:18,362 --> 00:14:19,988
before we get off of it.

176
00:14:20,072 --> 00:14:22,324
Yeah, all of us and the slaves.

177
00:14:24,117 --> 00:14:25,619
We'll need a bigger ship.

178
00:15:03,824 --> 00:15:04,950
<i>I'm catching too much heat!</i>

179
00:15:06,868 --> 00:15:08,870
<i>R-7, cut the engines!</i>

180
00:15:22,717 --> 00:15:25,637
Yeah ! That got 'em. Good work, General!

181
00:15:25,679 --> 00:15:29,182
Keep your focus, Warthog.
Watch out for those towers!

182
00:15:50,245 --> 00:15:51,246
No!

183
00:15:54,291 --> 00:15:56,460
The walls, they're electrified.

184
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:40,253
The controls are destroyed, Master Plo.
There's nothing we can do from here!

185
00:16:43,048 --> 00:16:45,342
I cannot move the cruiser in
for the rescue operation

186
00:16:45,425 --> 00:16:47,844
until those enemy canons are destroyed.

187
00:16:47,928 --> 00:16:49,554
<i>We'll take care of those canons.</i>

188
00:16:49,638 --> 00:16:51,431
Just make sure
that cruiser gets down here.

189
00:16:51,473 --> 00:16:53,266
We're running out of time!

190
00:16:53,308 --> 00:16:56,436
I'm going to go help my people,
I'll see if I can buy us some time!

191
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,771
Good luck!

192
00:17:07,822 --> 00:17:08,865
Incoming!

193
00:17:28,718 --> 00:17:29,886
A Jedi!

194
00:17:58,915 --> 00:18:00,166
You're all clear, Master Plo.

195
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:02,168
Bring the cruiser down to the landing pad.

196
00:18:02,210 --> 00:18:03,837
<i>Cancel that order, Master!</i>

197
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:06,548
There's no way
to get the people out of the holding cell

198
00:18:06,631 --> 00:18:08,425
and up to the landing platform.

199
00:18:08,508 --> 00:18:09,593
But I have an idea.

200
00:18:09,676 --> 00:18:12,637
We need to have the cruiser move in
underneath the facility.

201
00:18:12,679 --> 00:18:16,725
We can escape onto the ship
if Admiral Coburn can get in close enough.

202
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:18,560
You heard Commander Tano.

203
00:18:18,643 --> 00:18:21,938
I want the men topside with rocket packs
and cable guns. Move it!

204
00:18:22,022 --> 00:18:23,273
Yes, sir!

205
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:43,960
Come now, Master Kenobi, I know
a Jedi won't kill an unarmed man!

206
00:18:50,634 --> 00:18:52,177
I'm no Jedi.

207
00:19:26,753 --> 00:19:30,256
Okay, everyone, get ready.
We'll have to go by groups!

208
00:19:52,445 --> 00:19:53,446
Gotcha.

209
00:20:06,793 --> 00:20:10,588
<i>That's everyone. We have to go.
The facility's breaking up!</i>

210
00:20:14,342 --> 00:20:16,678
Okay, Master Plo, the cruiser is clear!

211
00:20:16,928 --> 00:20:18,638
All gunships, fire!

212
00:20:49,419 --> 00:20:54,132
I thank you, the Jedi, and the Republic
for saving our lives.

213
00:20:54,549 --> 00:20:56,009
Ahsoka is the real hero.

214
00:20:56,092 --> 00:20:59,971
Without her creativity, I don't think
we would've gotten your people to safety.

215
00:21:00,346 --> 00:21:04,726
Indeed. Padawan Tano,
might I have a word in private?

216
00:21:05,185 --> 00:21:06,519
Of course.

217
00:21:12,317 --> 00:21:16,196
Ahsoka, you have done a great deed
for your people today.

218
00:21:16,696 --> 00:21:17,906
You're sad?

219
00:21:17,989 --> 00:21:21,159
Well, you and the Jedi have done your best,

220
00:21:21,201 --> 00:21:26,456
but I do not think our people will recover
from this horror anytime soon.

221
00:21:26,539 --> 00:21:29,167
I understand, but in the end,

222
00:21:29,209 --> 00:21:32,212
surviving this
will only strengthen the people.

223
00:21:32,253 --> 00:21:38,051
Perhaps, and perhaps the people of Kiros
will also join the Republic.

224
00:21:38,718 --> 00:21:41,012
I think that's a wise choice, Governor.

225
00:21:41,036 --> 00:21:46,036
http://hiqve.com/

